<ul>
<li>
<p>Defect Density =3D 5 defects / 1000 LOC =3D <strong>0.005</strong></p></=
li>
<li>
<p>DRE =3D 90% (means most bugs were caught before release).</p></li>
<li>
<p>MTBF =3D 200 hours (system fails once every ~200 hours).</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<p>=E2=9C=85 <strong>In summary</strong>:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>SQA</strong> =3D preventive + monitoring activities across SDLC.=
</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Quality Factors</strong> =3D attributes like reliability, usabil=
ity, maintainability.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Quality Measures</strong> =3D metrics (defect density, MTBF, DRE=
, CV, SV) to track &amp; improve quality.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<p>Would you like me to also draw a <strong>comparison table: SQA vs Softwa=
re Testing</strong> (since many confuse these two in exams/interviews)?</p>
<p></p>
<ol start=3D"15">
<li>
<p>Cost impact of Software defects.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Concepts of Software reliability, availability and safety.</p></li>
</ol>
<p>Perfect! Let=E2=80=99s go step by step and make it clear and practical.<=
/p>
<hr>
<h1 id=3D"SoftwareEngineeringandInformationSystemDesign-=F0=9F=94=B9CostImp=
actofSoftwareDefects">=F0=9F=94=B9 <strong>Cost Impact of Software Defects<=
/strong></h1>
<p>Software defects (bugs) can be extremely costly depending on <strong>whe=
n they are detected</strong> during the SDLC.</p>
<h3 id=3D"SoftwareEngineeringandInformationSystemDesign-1.CostEscalationOve=
rTime">1. <strong>Cost Escalation Over Time</strong></h3>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"ad=
dbc551-c4e0-4a73-a32b-39d5f91674a2" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Phase Defect Found</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Cost to Fix (relative)</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Explanation</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Requirements Phase</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>1x</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Easier &amp; cheaper to correct requirement mistakes early.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Design Phase</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>5x</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Fixing design issues costs more than changing requirements.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Implementation Phase</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>10x</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Code changes and unit retesting required.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Testing Phase</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>15=E2=80=9320x</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Integration &amp; regression tests needed after fixes.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Production / Post-release</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>100x+</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Fixing defects in live systems causes downtime, customer dissatisfaction=
, reputational damage, and expensive patches.</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p><strong>Example:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>A calculation bug in a banking app caught <strong>before release</strong=
> =E2=86=92 minor code change.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Same bug detected <strong>after millions of transactions processed</stro=
ng> =E2=86=92 huge financial loss, legal consequences, and emergency patche=
s.</p></li>
</ul>
<p>=E2=9C=85 <strong>Takeaway:</strong> =E2=80=9CThe earlier you detect def=
ects, the cheaper it is to fix.=E2=80=9D</p>
<hr>
<h1 id=3D"SoftwareEngineeringandInformationSystemDesign-=F0=9F=94=B9Concept=
sofSoftwareReliability,Availability,andSafety">=F0=9F=94=B9 <strong>Concept=
s of Software Reliability, Availability, and Safety</strong></h1>
<h3 id=3D"SoftwareEngineeringandInformationSystemDesign-1.SoftwareReliabili=
ty">1. <strong>Software Reliability</strong></h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Definition:</strong> Probability that software <strong>operates =
without failure</strong> for a specified period under given conditions.</p>=
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Metric:</strong> Mean Time Between Failures (MTBF)</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Example:</strong> ATM software that works <strong>24/7 for 200 d=
ays</strong> without crashing =E2=86=92 highly reliable.</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"SoftwareEngineeringandInformationSystemDesign-2.SoftwareAvailabil=
ity">2. <strong>Software Availability</strong></h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Definition:</strong> Probability that software is <strong>operat=
ional and accessible when required</strong>.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Metric:</strong></p></li>
</ul>
<p>Availability=3DMTBFMTBF+MTTRAvailability =3D \frac{MTBF}{MTBF + MTTR}</p=
>
<ul>
<li>
<p>MTBF =3D Mean Time Between Failures</p></li>
<li>
<p>MTTR =3D Mean Time to Repair</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Example:</strong> Online banking system:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>MTBF =3D 1000 hours, MTTR =3D 2 hours</p></li>
<li>
<p>Availability =3D 1000 / (1000 + 2) =E2=89=88 0.998 =E2=86=92 99.8% uptim=
e</p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"SoftwareEngineeringandInformationSystemDesign-3.SoftwareSafety">3=
. <strong>Software Safety</strong></h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Definition:</strong> Software=E2=80=99s ability to <strong>opera=
te without causing harm to people, property, or environment</strong>, even =
if failures occur.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Focus:</strong> Critical systems (aviation, medical devices, nuc=
lear plants).</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Example:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Medical infusion pump =E2=86=92 must <strong>not overdose</strong> patie=
nts even if a software glitch occurs.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Safety measures: input validation, redundancy, fail-safe mechanisms.</p>=
</li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h1 id=3D"SoftwareEngineeringandInformationSystemDesign-=F0=9F=94=B9VisualS=
ummary">=F0=9F=94=B9 <strong>Visual Summary</strong></h1>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Softwar=
e Quality Attributes:

Reliability  =E2=86=92 Does the system work consistently?
Availability =E2=86=92 Is the system operational when needed?
Safety       =E2=86=92 Does the system avoid causing harm even in failure?
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>Relation to Cost:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Poor reliability =E2=86=92 more downtime =E2=86=92 higher maintenance co=
st.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Poor availability =E2=86=92 lost business &amp; user dissatisfaction.</p=
></li>
<li>
<p>Poor safety =E2=86=92 legal liability, financial penalties, loss of repu=
tation.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<p>=E2=9C=85 <strong>Key Takeaways:</strong></p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p>Fix defects early =E2=86=92 <strong>reduce cost impact</strong>.</p></li=
>
<li>
<p>Reliability, availability, and safety are <strong>critical non-functiona=
l quality attributes</strong>.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Metrics like <strong>MTBF, MTTR, and uptime percentages</strong> help qu=
antify quality.</p></li>
</ol>
<hr>
<p>If you want, I can also create a <strong>table summarizing Reliability v=
s Availability vs Safety with examples, metrics, and impact on cost</strong=
> so it=E2=80=99s easier to memorize and use in exams.</p>
