<li>
<p>Function based metrics and bang metrics.</p></li>
</ol>
<p>Got it! Let=E2=80=99s go step by step and explain <strong>Function-Based=
 Metrics</strong> and <strong>Bang (BANG) Metrics</strong> clearly, with ex=
amples.</p>
<hr>
<h1 id=3D"SoftwareEngineeringandInformationSystemDesign-=F0=9F=94=B91.Funct=
ion-BasedMetrics">=F0=9F=94=B9 <strong>1. Function-Based Metrics</strong></=
h1>
<p><strong>Definition:</strong><br>
Function-based metrics are software metrics that <strong>measure the functi=
onality delivered by the software</strong> rather than lines of code. They =
are also called <strong>functional size metrics</strong>.</p>
<p><strong>Purpose:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Measure software size in terms of <strong>functionality</strong>.</p></l=
i>
<li>
<p>Useful for <strong>estimating effort, cost, and quality</strong>.</p></l=
i>
</ul>
<p><strong>Most Popular Method:</strong> <strong>Function Point Analysis (F=
PA)</strong></p>
<hr>
<h3 id=3D"SoftwareEngineeringandInformationSystemDesign-FunctionPointAnalys=
is(FPA)Steps:"><strong>Function Point Analysis (FPA) Steps:</strong></h3>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p>Identify <strong>functional components</strong>:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>External Inputs (EI) =E2=86=92 e.g., login form, order submission</p></l=
i>
<li>
<p>External Outputs (EO) =E2=86=92 e.g., reports, invoices</p></li>
<li>
<p>External Inquiries (EQ) =E2=86=92 e.g., search queries</p></li>
<li>
<p>Internal Logical Files (ILF) =E2=86=92 e.g., database tables</p></li>
<li>
<p>External Interface Files (EIF) =E2=86=92 e.g., external APIs</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p>Assign <strong>weight</strong> (Low, Medium, High) to each component.</p=
></li>
<li>
<p>Calculate <strong>Unadjusted Function Points (UFP)</strong>.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Adjust based on <strong>14 general system characteristics</strong> (comp=
lexity factors like performance, security).</p></li>
<li>
<p>Result =E2=86=92 <strong>Adjusted Function Points (AFP)</strong></p></li=
>
</ol>
<p>=E2=9C=85 <strong>Example:</strong><br>
A simple e-commerce system:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>10 External Inputs (login, add to cart, checkout)</p></li>
<li>
<p>5 External Outputs (invoice, email notification)</p></li>
<li>
<p>3 Internal Files (Product DB, User DB, Orders DB)</p></li>
</ul>
<p>=E2=86=92 Total Function Points =3D sum of weighted components =3D <stro=
ng>50 FP (example)</strong></p>
<p><strong>Benefits:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Language-independent (Java, C++, Python doesn=E2=80=99t matter).</p></li=
>
<li>
<p>Better for <strong>estimating cost and effort</strong> than LOC (Lines o=
f Code).</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h1 id=3D"SoftwareEngineeringandInformationSystemDesign-=F0=9F=94=B92.BANGM=
etrics">=F0=9F=94=B9 <strong>2. BANG Metrics</strong></h1>
<p><strong>Definition:</strong><br>
BANG Metrics is a <strong>software complexity and quality metric</strong> b=
ased on <strong>Branch, Assignment, Number of Loops, and Global variables</=
strong>.<br>
It is mostly used in <strong>white-box testing</strong> and <strong>code co=
mplexity analysis</strong>.</p>
<p><strong>Components of BANG Metrics:</strong></p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"5d=
f02cf0-5317-4377-b1d7-afc3c89aa11e" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Metric Component</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Description</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>B (Branch)</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Number of decision points (if, switch, case).</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>A (Assignment)</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Number of assignments in the code.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>N (Number of Loops)</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Number of loops (for, while, do-while).</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>G (Global Variables)</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Number of global variables used.</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p><strong>Formula / Score:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>BANG Score</strong> =3D B + A + N + G</p></li>
<li>
<p>Higher score =E2=86=92 more complex code =E2=86=92 harder to maintain an=
d test.</p></li>
</ul>
<p>=E2=9C=85 <strong>Example (Java):</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">int sum=
Array(int[] arr) {         // BANG count starts
    int sum =3D 0;                  // Assignment (A=3D1)
    for(int i=3D0; i&lt;arr.length; i++) { // Loop (N=3D1)
        if(arr[i] &gt; 0) {          // Branch (B=3D1)
            sum +=3D arr[i];        // Assignment (A=3D2)
        }
    }
    return sum;
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<ul>
<li>
<p>B =3D 1 (if condition)</p></li>
<li>
<p>A =3D 2 (sum initialization + sum +=3D arr[i])</p></li>
<li>
<p>N =3D 1 (for loop)</p></li>
<li>
<p>G =3D 0 (no global variable)</p></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>BANG Score</strong> =3D 1 + 2 + 1 + 0 =3D <strong>4</strong></p>
<p><strong>Interpretation:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Higher BANG =E2=86=92 more complex =E2=86=92 higher testing effort, hard=
er maintenance.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Can guide <strong>refactoring and quality improvement</strong>.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h1 id=3D"SoftwareEngineeringandInformationSystemDesign-=F0=9F=94=B9Summary=
Table">=F0=9F=94=B9 <strong>Summary Table</strong></h1>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"07=
ce872f-4203-4cb8-be5e-5ed1d35e2a10" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Metric Type</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Basis</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Example</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Usage</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Function-Based</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Functionality delivered</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Function Point Analysis (login, checkout, invoice)</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Estimating effort, cost, size, quality</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>BANG Metrics</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Code complexity (Branch, Assignment, Loops, Globals)</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Java code with loops, if-else, assignments</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Measuring complexity, maintainability, testing effort</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<hr>
<p>=F0=9F=92=A1 <strong>Key Takeaway:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Function-based metrics</strong> =E2=86=92 Focus on <strong>what =
the software does</strong>.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>BANG metrics</strong> =E2=86=92 Focus on <strong>how the softwar=
e is implemented</strong> and its complexity.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<p>If you want, I can also <strong>draw a small diagram showing Function Me=
trics vs BANG Metrics and their relation to Cost, Complexity, and Testing E=
ffort</strong> for easy memorization.</p>
<p>Do you want me to do that?</p>
<p></p>
<ol start=3D"18">
<li>
<p>Metrics for analysis and design model. Metrics for source code, testing =
and maintenance</p></li>
</ol>
<p>Perfect! Let=E2=80=99s go step by step and cover <strong>metrics for ana=
lysis &amp; design, source code, testing, and maintenance</strong> with exa=
mples and clear explanations.</p>
<hr>
<h1 id=3D"SoftwareEngineeringandInformationSystemDesign-=F0=9F=94=B91.Metri=
csforAnalysisandDesignModels">=F0=9F=94=B9 <strong>1. Metrics for Analysis =
and Design Models</strong></h1>
<p>These metrics <strong>measure quality, complexity, and effectiveness</st=
rong> of software models (like UML diagrams, ER diagrams, DFDs) <strong>bef=
ore coding</strong>.</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"7e=
aeb9f3-9990-49e5-ab6d-30635427dcd5" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Metric</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Definition</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Example / Use</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Number of Classes (NOC)</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Count of classes in UML/Class diagram</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>UML diagram has 10 classes =E2=86=92 NOC =3D 10</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Number of Relationships (NOR)</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Count of associations, aggregations, dependencies</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>12 relationships between classes =E2=86=92 NOR =3D 12</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Depth of Inheritance Tree (DIT)</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Max inheritance levels in class hierarchy</p></td>
